Title: Getting Hands on With Linux
Book Description: Who put the penguin in Penguicon? You did! Come get hands on with Linux with one of our favorite presenters. Tom Lawrence will guide attendees through the ins and outs of Linux for home and office use. Noteworthy addendum! There will be 20 laptops available in the lab. First come- first served.

Title: Open Linux Computer Lab (Unconference)
Book Description: Open Computer lab utilizing the Unconference philopsophy of Open Space Technology. Bring your projects to discuss. Bring your discussions to projects. Attendees may also puruse social media- tweet to #Penguicon- browse the whole internet and get a feel for Linux using one of our 20 laptops.

Title: Hands on Python for Everything and Everybody
Book Description: Join MDLUG and friends to walk through an introductory course on building small useful scripts in Python. Get your hands dirty in the fertile soil that is sprouting some of the most interesting developments in machine learning- server scripting and automation! Noteworthy addendum! There will be 20 laptops available in the lab. First come- first served.

Title: All Hands Active Embedded Software
Book Description: Our 2016 Charity- All Hands Active- will talk about the development of the Penguicon Uber Badge. They will demonstrate PCB Board Development with open source tools and demonstrate arduino programming from the ground up. Noteworthy addendum! There will be 20 laptops available in the lab. First come- first served.

Title: The Traveling Circus: Intro to Coding Workshop
Presenters: Chioke Mose-Telesford, Aaron Wolff, Aisha Blake
Book Description: We recognize coding can be a bit intimidating. You might have dabbled on the web with some free coding programs- but run into a road-block without the support of an instructor. That's where our Intro to Coding Workshop- lovingly called  “The Traveling Circus-” comes in. This is designed for folks who are curious about coding- but who have little to no experience. You'll walk away with some programming foundations to start learning on your own!
